July 21, 2019 I went to mist to have brunch to celebrate my sister birthday with friends, a party of six in total. We had a 3pm reservation which wasn’t valid because soon as you walk in you pay upon arrival and your told you can sit anywhere. So if your party is big and all the large tables are being used it’s just gonna be an unfortunate situation for you, luckily we found a table for six people. Back to arrival so your given two brunch options unlimited food buffet and drinks for 90 minutes 45$ or unlimited food buffet and drinks for the whole night up until 7pm 55$. We were also told after 7pm the brunch ends, the day party starts and you can purchase drinks from the bar. This was false because the place business hours says they close at 7pm on Sundays which I found out once 7pm came. So we go to the buffet and are told  all the food is not unlimited. However the workers at the front who charge you and give you a wrist band failed to mention all the food was not unlimited. So “MIST” is offering unlimited brunch buffet when it’s not true. So your unlimited options are eggs, bacon, salad, fruit salad, sweet potato fries, pork, jerk chicken. The options you can only get ONE TIME from the buffet are fried chicken, wack n cheese, shrimp, rice & peas. There are no waiters for any tables , no one offers water for any table nor drinks you have to go back and fourth to a crowded bar. Drinks are not good. Bottom shelf liquor extremely cheap liquor which caused three of my friends to throw up that same night once home. Food isn’t great. a black worker made a racist slur against a white man which I did not like because he attempted to serve himself during the buffet which they don’t allow you to do so like all buffets do, it’s always a professional way to handle things. A photographer was going around the room taking pictures of guest eating and drinking, this man told me and my friends the day party starts at 7pm he will see us in there. So we eat, socialize by 7 we decide to head to the back room where they have the dance floor but to our surprise it was no dj, no music, no guests. So I approach the owner to inquire about the things I was told and how much we have been misinformed since we got to the restaurant, as I did he was dealing with another group of women who did not seem happy and was crying and going off. I was not heard and understood at all. My approach was very respectful. Not one time did I hear an “I apologize “! The owner pretty much made me feel like it was my fault for being misinformed, yet he has people walking around his establishment taking pictures of their guest and talking about a day party as well as people at his front desk giving out the wrong information to guest and charging them for services they are not gonna receive. He was not kind at all. It’s just an unfortunate situation being a black female in America trying to support black business. I got so frustrated trying to explain myself and being heard and understood to the point i cried and decided to leave because the situation hurt me. To be treated by your own kind in a horrible manor is just sad and heart breaking, when all you are trying to do is support them. my whole experience at mist was horrible and I would never return, I don’t recommend this place for anyone unless things change for the better.
